FT  06 AUG 92 / UK Company News: British Data Management
British Data Management has paid Pounds 1.45m cash for the data storage
business of Exclusive Group, a wholly-owned subsidiary of Graig Shipping.
The assets acquired include the goodwill, fixtures and fittings with a net
book value of some Pounds 130,000 and the benefit of the 156 ongoing storage
contracts currently managed by Exclusive.
The contracts generate storage turnover of some Pounds 590,000 per annum. In
addition, a further Pounds 100,000 a year is generated from the management
and retrieval of the data stored under the contracts.
